      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: install GitHub-backed ClawHub skills",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Resolve ClawHub installs through `/api/v1/skills/:slug/install` when no explicit version is requested.\n- Support GitHub-backed install resolutions by downloading the resolved repo commit from GitHub codeload and copying only the resolved skill path into the local skills directory.\n- Preserve the latest install-policy checks for both ClawHub archive installs and GitHub-backed installs.\n- Report authenticated install telemetry to ClawHub after successful installs.\n- Add unit and E2E coverage for GitHub-backed ClawHub skill installs.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:src`\n- `bunx vitest run src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts src/cli/skills-cli.clawhub-install.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n",
